article.headline: N. Colorado 65, Weber St. 46
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. -- Elliott Lloyd scored 16 points as Northern Colorado ran its winning streak to seven with a 65-46 victory over Weber State on Saturday night. Chris Kaba and Neal Kingman added 12 points apiece for the Bears (11-7, 7-0 Big Sky), who made 9 of 23 from 3-point range. Lloyd sank 3 of 4, and Kaba went 2 of 4. Lloyd also had six assists. Scott Bamforth led the Wildcats (9-9, 3-4) with 19 points, including 5 of 8 on 3-pointers. But no teammate scored more than seven points. Kyle Bullinger had team-leading totals of seven rebounds and four assists. Mike Proctor grabbed eight rebounds to lead Northern Colorado to a 38-27 advantage on the boards. Northern Colorado built a 43-20 halftime lead and was never in serious trouble.
